lessons.theory:
## Go Functions
Go functions can return multiple values!

```go
// Basic function
func add(a int, b int) int {
    return a + b
}

// Shorthand parameters
func multiply(a, b int) int {
    return a * b
}

// Multiple returns
func divide(a, b float64) (float64, error) {
    if b == 0 {
        return 0, fmt.Errorf("divide by zero")
    }
    return a / b, nil
}
```

